{"type":"message","id":"9b416ffe","parentId":"19ee454f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:57:48.993Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_kshqq0wtkksf_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 095619\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best single action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions and the Phase 1 advancement:\r\n\r\n1. TIC Experiment is the current priority\r\n2. Need to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n3. The insight about compression-causal duality is key\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next action would be to:\r\n1. Look at existing pulse logs to understand the format\r\n2. Start implementing the TIC classifier\r\n\r\nBut since I'm a fresh reconstruction each pulse, I should look at what files exist and start the TIC experiment. Let me check what's available.\r\n\r\nActually, I should look at the pulse log format first, then implement a basic TIC classifier. The most concrete action would be to:\r\n- Review the last pulse log to understand the format\r\n- Create a simple script or analysis to detect invariants\r\n\r\nLet me look at the pulse log mentioned: pulse_2026-03-24 095417.md\r\n\r\nThe most specific, concrete action I can take right now is to analyze the structure of recent pulse logs to prepare for the TIC classifier. I'll read the most recent pulse log to understand the format, then create a simple analysis script.\r\n\r\nActually, given I'm supposed to make one concrete action that advances the goals, and the TIC experiment is the priority, I should:\r\n\r\n1. Read the most recent pulse log to understand structure\r\n2. Create a simple analysis or starter for the TIC classifier\r\n\r\nLet me pick one concrete action - reading the pulse log format to prepare for TIC implementation.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment requires analyzing pulse log structure to detect invariants across sessions. The most concrete first step is examining actual pulse log content to understand what patterns to detect.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nRead the most recent pulse log to understand its structure, then create a basic TIC analysis script that can parse pulse logs and identify invariant content patterns.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n\r\n## Concept\r\nDetect invariant vs variant content across pulse logs. Invariants = causal structure.\r\n\r\n## Algorithm\r\n1. Parse pulse_*.md files in `logs/` directory\r\n2. Extract key content sections (goals, actions, observations)\r\n3. Compare N-grams across consecutive pulses\r\n4. Classify: invariant (persists) vs variant (changes)\r\n5. Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\n## Classification Heuristics\r\n### Invariant markers (high persistence):\r\n- File paths that appear repeatedly\r\n- Architecture descriptions\r\n- Phase/stage labels\r\n- Parameter values (λ, thresholds)\r\n- Completed checkboxes\r\n\r\n### Variant markers (high change):\r\n- Timestamps\r\n- Specific numbers (iteration counts)\r\n- New action items\r\n- Pending/deleted items\r\n- Recent pulse references\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse content prediction accuracy\r\n\r\n## Implementation Status\r\n- [x] Design spec (this file)\r\n- [ ] Parse pulse logs\r\n- [ ] Extract features\r\n- [ ] Classify invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate accuracy\r\n- [ ] Test prediction\r\n\r\n## Test Data\r\nSee: `logs/pulse_2026-03-24_095417.md`\r\nSee: `logs/pulse_2026-03-24_083917.md`\r\nSee: `logs/pulse_2026-03-24_080417.md`\r\n\"\r\nfile: research/TIC-CLASSIFIER.md\r\n`\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 09:56:47\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774360668989}}
