{"type":"message","id":"740b5450","parentId":"002280b2","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:59:03.303Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_p92kyyjeubyy_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 095715\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/TIC-CLASSIFIER.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the next concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n\r\nKey pending item:\r\n- **TIC Experiment (Next Action)**\r\n  - Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n  - Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n  - Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n  - Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe key insight is \"COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\" - that causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\n\r\nThe next concrete action should be to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on the pulse log files. This is a specific, achievable task.\r\n\r\nI should create a script that:\r\n1. Reads the pulse log files\r\n2. Implements TIC classification (identifies invariant vs variant content)\r\n3. Measures accuracy against success criteria\r\n\r\nLet me create a TIC experiment script that can analyze the pulse logs.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment is the next concrete step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns across pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `scripts/tic_experiment.ps1` - a PowerShell script that analyzes pulse logs for temporal invariance patterns, classifies invariant/variant content, and measures prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% next-pulse prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n# Tests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [string]$LogPattern = \"logs/pulse_*.md\",\r\n    [double]$InvarianceThreshold = 0.7\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Experiment ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Hypothesis: Causal structure = Invariant structure\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Testing: Pulse log temporal invariance patterns\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# Collect pulse logs sorted by timestamp\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogPattern | Sort-Object Name\r\nWrite-Host \"Found $($pulseFiles.Count) pulse logs\"\r\n\r\nif ($pulseFiles.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Host \"ERROR: Need at least 5 pulse logs for TIC analysis\" -ForegroundColor Red\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Parse pulse content into structured data\r\nfunction Parse-Pulse {\r\n    param([string]$Path)\r\n    \r\n    $content = Get-Content $Path -Raw\r\n    $lines = $content -split \"`n\"\r\n    \r\n    # Extract key elements\r\n    $observation = \"\"\r\n    $action = \"\"\r\n    $mutation = \"\"\r\n    $inMutation = $false\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($line in $lines) {\r\n        if ($line -match \"^### OBSERVATION\") { $inMutation = $false }\r\n        elseif ($line -match \"^### ACTION\") { $inMutation = $false }\r\n        elseif ($line -match \"^### MUTATION\") { $inMutation = $true; $mutation = \"\" }\r\n        elseif ($line -match \"^### \" -and $inMutation) { $inMutation = $false }\r\n        elseif ($inMutation) { $mutation += $line + \"`n\" }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return @{\r\n        Path = $Path\r\n        Content = $content\r\n        Lines = $lines\r\n        Length = $content.Length\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n$pulses = $pulseFiles | ForEach-Object { Parse-Pulse $_.FullName }\r\n\r\n# Extract n-gram patterns (bigrams) from pulse content\r\nfunction Get-NGrams {\r\n    param([string]$Text, [int]$N = 2)\r\n    \r\n    $words = $Text -split '\\s+' | Where-Object { $_.Length -gt 3 }\r\n    $ngrams = @()\r\n    \r\n    for ($i = 0; $i -lt $words.Count - $N; $i++) {\r\n        $ngram = ($words[$i..($i + $N - 1)] -join \" \").ToLower()\r\n        $ngrams += $ngram\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return $ngrams\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Count n-gram frequencies across all pulses\r\n$globalNgrams = @{}\r\nforeach ($pulse in $pulses) {\r\n    $ngrams = Get-NGrams $pulse.Content\r\n    foreach ($ngram in $ngrams) {\r\n        if ($globalNgrams.ContainsKey($ngram)) {\r\n            $globalNgrams[$ngram]++\r\n        } else {\r\n            $globalNgrams[$ngram] = 1\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Classify n-grams as INVARIANT (appear in multiple pulses) or VARIANT (unique)\r\n$invariantNgrams = @{}\r\n$variantNgrams = @{}\r\n\r\nforeach ($key in $globalNgrams.Keys) {\r\n    if ($globalNgrams[$key] -ge 2) {\r\n        $invariantNgrams[$key] = $globalNgrams[$key]\r\n    } else {\r\n        $variantNgrams[$key] = $globalNgrams[$key]\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\nWrite-Host \"N-gram Analysis:\" -ForegroundColor Yellow\r\nWrite-Host \"  Total unique n-grams: $($globalNgrams.Count)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"  Invariant n-grams (≥2 occurrences): $($invariantNgrams.Count)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"  Variant n-grams (1 occurrence): $($variantNgrams.Count)\"\r\n\r\n# Calculate invariance ratio\r\n$invarianceRatio = if ($globalNgrams.Count -gt 0) { \r\n    $invariantNgrams.Count\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 09:57:48\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774360743301}}
